This executive order, issued on January 19, 2021, focuses on veterans and includes the following provisions:

Section 1: The Secretary of Veterans Affairs, in consultation with the Secretary of Defense, is directed to consider designating veterans who served on active duty in Uzbekistan between October 1, 2001, and December 31, 2005, as veterans who served on active duty in a theater of combat operations.

Section 2: Within 365 days of the order, the Secretary of Defense is instructed to conduct a study on toxic exposure to members of the Armed Forces deployed to the Karshi-Khanabad Air Base in Uzbekistan between October 1, 2001, and December 31, 2005. The study should include an assessment of the conditions at the Air Base during that period, identification of any toxic substances present, and an epidemiological study of the health consequences for the affected service members.

Section 3: This section includes general provisions stating that the order does not affect the authority of executive departments or agencies, the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and that it should be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations. It also clarifies that the order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.

The order is signed by Donald J. Trump and was issued from The White House on January 19, 2021.